The difference in the case of the safe voters of the parties - due to the greater firmness of the opposition voters - would mean support of more than two thirds (a 71 percent) against the support of one fifth for the socialists (a 20 percent).
According to the survey, the Democratic Forum and the Alliance of Free Democrats would not reach the necessary limit to have any parliamentary seats: their support within the entire population is two percent.
Among the safe voters there is one percent more sympathizers on both sides.
