Comparatively, in "general elections to be held this Sunday" only 55 percent of the population would participate safely and another 15 percent would probably believe their participation. Based on the current intentions of the voters there is no doubt of the result of the popular consultation.
Some 74 per cent of the population would disapprove of the payment of education rights, 79 per cent of the medical services and 84 per cent of hospital care.
If we observed these proportions only among the safe participants in the referendum, 81, 84 and 89 per cent of voters would reject the introduction of education rights, payment for medical consultations and hospital care.
