Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
In parallel with its parliamentary process, which ended today with the vote by Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft Senate, the Government has submitted to the public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim that both will enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation in order to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activity of entities to ensure that markets operate efficiently.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, implies the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improves the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (NCMV) and promotes cooperation between the various European Union supervisors.
The new regulations will provide financial advisory services to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services firm (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFI), which join value companies, securities agencies and portfolio managers.
In addition, it expands the number of financial instrument execution systems, so that regulated secondary markets are accompanied by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment service companies to disseminate information on the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they perform, to facilitate the supervision by the NCMV.
In its passage through the Committee on the Economy of Congress, several amendments were incorporated, including the fact that debt titrated is considered as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with the debt of high risk mortgages in the United States (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally define the functions of graduates in Economics and Business 30 years after the actual decree defining the professional functions reserved for economists was adopted in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of others, will not require the authorization of CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer picking services to different investment firms at the same time.
